by Valentine Z » Thu Jan 21, 2021 8:06 am

Synne Industries wrote:CFC-JSCD1-002 Jerichos (Jerichoes?) incorporate NCAF, a sort of weird nano composite which takes the place of flesh, a skeleton, and really a lot of things in its humanoid construction. Being composed of nanomechanical bots which are themselves composed of many other things, the material is able to harden in response to physical trauma son, greatly reducing the damage inflicted by brute kinetic force. This allows the energy to be distributed across a large mass of NCAF so that actual loss in nanite functionality from damage is minimized. The stuff's good at dealing with bullets, harsh environments, EMPs, and DEWs, but what it isn't good at dealing with is plasma. This is where its armor comes in, the platey bits that stop the Jerichos from just looking like gray goopy people. The plating is a composite which incorporates Lunar Titanium which is a better hurt-stopper. I know it probably has to go through some fancy fabrication process before it ends up on a drone but it's still gonna be my headcanon that they just slap whatever they've peeled off of a dead spaceship onto a Jericho. Gives em' a bit more soul y'know.

As a short one-liner first, I wonder what happened to all the crazy and weird tech stuff with large numbers that would make a computer blush (or run into error, because there are too many numbers). Definitely a retcon at work.

So one of the things I have learned about Synne Industries today - Non-Government Defense. The fact that they have private military companies and security contractors to aid in the defense of their own country. That itself is good enough, and thankfully, I am just glad that Synne Industries only do defensive work and tasks with these people. I don't want to once again play on the trope of how private military companies are unethical - I am sure that if I read more, there are companies and private armies that at least has some resemblance of ethics. So yeah, it's nice to see the mercenaries, at least from what I have read, doing something nice and defensive instead of going all-out offensive.

That, and the Synnian Self-Defense Army is the smallest branch of the Synnian Armed Forces in terms of equipment, mostly relegated to duties on Synnian soil. It would seem like you are relying a little too much on the private contractors for self-defense. If RL Singapore is anything to go by with external help, I would recommend SSDA having more numbers and force.

-----

Gemeanwealth of Man wrote:Despite the fact the Star State's very existence is justified upon the extermination of all non-human life, nearly one out of every five sapient being in the territory under its nominal control is still non-human, with one out of every fifty a "near-human", though no further information of what these near-humans are could be found.

Perhaps learning that their First Contact with the aliens was less than stellar, and yeah, opening up to more trouble as time goes by. Man, what a gateway that opens to, as if the fight between the humans weren't enough.

And learning about the economy, and I quote: "The commonwealth's private sector and its gargantuan semi-private sectors control entire systems' worth of resources, with Holding Collectives -small conglomerates of varied industries- own all resources in entire star systems, while various number of worlds -and offworld deep space arcologies- have been dedicated to varied sectors of the economy, designated Forge Worlds, Industrial Worlds, Mining Worlds and Agri-Worlds."

I'm just wondering if most of their industries really only do come from these places, being a space empire, or that there are other things that they actually weirdly profit from. Taking a page from Comerciante, I wonder if stationery was still needed in space because hey, there are times when you really could use that pen and paper! I won't be surprised if one day humanity as a whole went galactic and our export is fast food because aliens just can't resist.
